# Writing punctuation

Do **not** use the em dash (`—`) or en dash (`–`) as punctuation in this project.

Use a **plain hyphen** (`-`) instead, with spaces when it separates phrases.

## Applies to

- User-facing UI copy (labels, toasts, errors, empty states)
- AI replies to the user in chat
- Docs and comments when writing for humans (README, AGENTS.md, `.lovable/*.md`)

Code identifiers, URLs, and third-party quoted text are unchanged.

## Replace

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `Masuk — ChatCRM` | `Masuk - ChatCRM` |
| `Demo mode — pilih role` | `Demo mode - pilih role` |
| `Login gagal — coba lagi` | `Login gagal - coba lagi` |
| `Opsi A — Lovable Cloud` | `Opsi A - Lovable Cloud` |

## When a hyphen is not enough

- Use a **comma**, **colon**, or **period** instead of a long dash
- Or split into two short sentences

## Examples

```
// Bad
Belum punya akun? Hubungi owner — kami kirim undangan via email.

// Good
Belum punya akun? Hubungi owner. Undangan dikirim via email.
```

```
// Bad (AI reply)
Auth sudah benar — tidak ada public register — invite owner-only.

// Good
Auth sudah benar. Tidak ada public register; invite owner-only.
```

Before finishing any task that adds or edits copy, grep changed files for `—` and `–` and replace with `-` or rephrase.
